<p class="mt4">
  Ember addon that provides a component which uses Google Places API to autocomplete place information when someone writes an address in a text field.
</p>
<p>
  It is very simple and gives you all the information of a place from Google, you can do whatever you want with that information using a callback function or using the service functions.
</p>
<img alt="example" src="http://i.imgur.com/wzGgfiY.gif">
<p>
  This addon provides two strategies to be able to communicate with Google place autocomplete services.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <h3 class="f5">place-autocomplete-field component</h3>
    <p>This component is a input text field that fetches google place predictions while the user is typing.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <h3 class="f5">google-place-autocomplete service</h3>
    <p>
      Instead of using the well known Google place autocomplete service, it is possible to use a google service which provides more flexibility when communicating with Google Places API. This services use the <strong><i>sessionToken</i></strong> by default in order to try to reduce the cost of paid services when getting places information.
    </p>
  </li>
</ul>
